The paper deals with the automatic generation of furniture layouts for indoor environments, which is a topic that falls under computer graphics (cs.GR) and computer vision (cs.CV). The method proposed involves learning joint statistics from a database of training layouts, which is a machine learning (cs.AI) technique. The paper also discusses the incorporation of constraints, which is a topic relevant to optimization (cs.LG) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
